{"title":"Boyd Cycling Prologue Series takes off with new affordable MTB & Road alloy wheelsets","link":"https://bikerumor.com/boyd-cycling-prologue-series-takes-off-with-new-affordable-mtb-road-alloy-wheelsets/","date":1639586978000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-scaled.jpeg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Boyd Rouleur Alloy Disc wheel. Hub view.\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194055/Boyd-road-2-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280636\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><div title=\"Page 1\" itemprop=\"text\"><div><p>Boyd Cycling’s budget-friendly Prologue Series wheelsets just got even friendlier.</p><div id=\"attachment_280637\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280637\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933.jpeg\" alt=\"Boyd Rouleur Alloy Disc wheel. Detail view.\" width=\"1747\" height=\"1177\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933.jpeg 1747w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933-297x200.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933-800x539.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933-120x81.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933-768x517.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194047/Boyd-road-1-scaled-e1639586168933-1536x1035.jpeg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1747px) 100vw, 1747px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280637\">The Boyd Rouleur Alloy Disc wheelset is the brand’s latest affordable wheel upgrade option.</p></div><p>In addition to its 28 and 44 mm <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/boyd-prologue-series-sizes-prices-weights-specs/\">carbon rim and disc Prologue wheelsets that launched in 2020</a>, Boyd has expanded with two new alloy models it hopes will bridge the gap between price tag and performance.</p><div id=\"attachment_280639\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280639\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149.jpeg\" alt=\"Boyd Rouleur Alloy Disc wheel. Full side view.\" width=\"1651\" height=\"1337\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149.jpeg 1651w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149-297x241.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149-800x648.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149-120x97.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149-768x622.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194104/Boyd-road-3-scaled-e1639586196149-1536x1244.jpeg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1651px) 100vw, 1651px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280639\">Boyd’s Rouleur Alloy Disc is built to be an everyday workhorse.</p></div><p>The new models include the road Rouler Alloy Disc, and the Stumphouse Alloy MTB wheelsets. Compared to the MSRP $1,050 of the carbon Prologue Series wheels, the alloy options go for MSRP $425 to $450, making them a truly affordable option for riders who want to replace stock wheels or find a solid replacement after a crash.</p></div><div><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195303/Boyd-Rouleur-spec-e1639586248644.jpg\" alt=\"Boyd Rouleur dimension graphic.\" width=\"1169\" height=\"751\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195303/Boyd-Rouleur-spec-e1639586248644.jpg 1169w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195303/Boyd-Rouleur-spec-e1639586248644-297x191.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195303/Boyd-Rouleur-spec-e1639586248644-800x514.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195303/Boyd-Rouleur-spec-e1639586248644-120x77.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195303/Boyd-Rouleur-spec-e1639586248644-768x493.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1169px) 100vw, 1169px\">The Rouleur rim weighs in at 460 grams and includes Skyuka hubs, Pillar TB2018 spokes, and brass nipples. Fully built, the wheel weighs 1760 grams. It’s fully tubeless compatible.</p><p>Specs:</p><ul><li>Spoke Count: 24 front, 28 rear</li><li>Thru axle: 12 x 100 front, 12 x 142 rear</li><li>Wheel size: 700c</li></ul><p>Boyd said the Rouleur isn’t designed to be extremely fancy, rather, it’s an everyday workhorse that won’t let riders down.</p><div id=\"attachment_280640\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280640\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304.jpeg\" alt=\"Boyd Stumphouse Alloy wheel. Detail view.\" width=\"1606\" height=\"1056\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304.jpeg 1606w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304-297x195.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304-800x526.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304-120x79.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304-768x505.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194114/Boyd-stumphouse-1-scaled-e1639586429304-1536x1010.jpeg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1606px) 100vw, 1606px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280640\">Boyd’s Stumphouse Alloy MTB wheel set is focused on durability and strength.</p></div><p>For those who spend their time on singletrack, Boyd has released the Alloy Stumphouse MTB. The Stumphouse comes in 29 or 27.5 inch options and features a 30mm rim that is also tubeless compatible and comes in boost or non-boost spacing.</p><div id=\"attachment_280641\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280641\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356.jpeg\" alt=\"Boyd Stumphouse Alloy wheel. Side view\" width=\"1651\" height=\"1331\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356.jpeg 1651w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356-297x239.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356-800x645.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356-120x97.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356-768x619.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09194123/Boyd-stumphouse-3-scaled-e1639586467356-1536x1238.jpeg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1651px) 100vw, 1651px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280641\">The Boyd Stumphouse wheelset is available in 29 or 27.5-inch options.</p></div><p>Boyd says the Stumphouse is design focused on durability and strength so riders can feel confident blasting off into the chunk. The Stumphouse includes Skyuba MTB hubs that come with tool-free service and interchanging among Hyperglide, Sram XS, and Shimano Microspline.</p><p>Specs:</p><ul><li>Spoke count: 32 front, 32 rear</li><li>Thru axle: 15 x 100 front, 12 x 142 rear</li><li>Wheel size: 27.5, 29</li></ul></div><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195305/Boyd-Stumphouse-spec-e1639586552353.jpg\" alt=\"Boyd Stumphouse dimension graphic.\" width=\"1227\" height=\"827\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195305/Boyd-Stumphouse-spec-e1639586552353.jpg 1227w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195305/Boyd-Stumphouse-spec-e1639586552353-297x200.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195305/Boyd-Stumphouse-spec-e1639586552353-800x539.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195305/Boyd-Stumphouse-spec-e1639586552353-120x81.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/09195305/Boyd-Stumphouse-spec-e1639586552353-768x518.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1227px) 100vw, 1227px\">The Rouleur is available for MSRP $425. The Stumphouse costs $450.</p></div></article></div></div>","author":"Mark Wilson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"0334a5f0ec4deb69bda6e6577bfbd6b8fcc79b72abca971ca2d37f82bf09a604","category":"Cycling"}